<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Cranston</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">A master planned community located in the south-east quadrant of Calgary in Alberta, Cranston is bounded by the Deerfoot Trail on the east, the Bow River on the south, the Fish Creek Park on the west and the Stoney Trail on the north.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Homes for sale in Cranston comprise a mix of single-family and multifamily residential units that enjoy spectacular views of the Bow River Valley and the surrounding Rockies. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Cranstonâ€™s homes are mostly single-detached and attached homes, making up a massive 99.3% of the real estate, with the remainder being a mixture of apartments and townhouses. 2.3% of the housing in Cranston is being used for rental purposes. As of 2011, Cranston has an estimated population of 10, 381.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">You can choose from the variety of housing options that are available within a price range of around $500,000 to as high as a million and a half.</p>
        </div>
